üü© STEP-1: Create a batch file (run-consumer.bat)

Create this file:

C:\kafka_2.13-2.8.1-SMM\run-consumer.bat


Put EXACTLY this inside (copy‚Äìpaste):

@echo off
set BOOTSTRAP=dev-kafka-cluster-kafka-bootstrap-dev-kafka.apps.dev.sbiepay.sbi:443
set TOPIC=smm
set CONFIG=C:\kafka_2.13-2.8.1-SMM\kafka_2.13-2.8.1\config\client.properties

C:\kafka_2.13-2.8.1-SMM\kafka_2.13-2.8.1\bin\windows\kafka-console-consumer.bat --bootstrap-server %BOOTSTRAP% --topic %TOPIC% --consumer.config "%CONFIG%" --from-beginning


Save ‚Üí close.



üü© STEP-2: Run it from CMD:
C:\kafka_2.13-2.8.1-SMM\run-consumer.bat


‚úî CMD will NOT parse a long line
‚úî The .bat file will
‚úî No syntax errors
‚úî No ‚Äúinput line too long‚Äù
‚úî This WILL WORK

üü¶ STEP-3: Create producer script (run-producer.bat)

